      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TELERN LOFTY (5) resumes from a spell of 11 months but showed ability last campaign and went to the paddock off back-to-back wins. Likely to have developed further with maturity and was readied by placing in two recent trials so could pick up where he left off. SKYFALL BENCHMARK (4) is an honest gelding who has put together a string of top-three finishes on either side of a spell  Kicked off this campaign with a Cobram win and has placed in his two Shepparton outings since. Has had a month off but expect another strong showing. MICHEN ROY (7) draws wide has been thereabouts in stronger races since coming from the back line to win at this venue. SORRISO DE PRAIA (3) ended the short maiden campaign with a win at Swan Hill 11 months ago. Readied with a trial win and has upside so is capable of a forward showing.",
